keyFacts: The document is a confidential TECS Person Encounter List generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on April 6, 2021.
It contains 30 travel records for an individual (whose name is redacted) spanning from 2004 to 2019.
The travel pattern shows frequent flights between Los Angeles (LAX) and London (LHR), with additional trips to/from Miami, Nassau, Vancouver, Manila, and New York.
The records utilize both APIS (Advanced Passenger Information System) and non-APIS airline data for tracking.
The document is marked as part of the SDNY (Southern District of New York) case materials, indicating its relevance to the Epstein investigation.
